Role: Act as a Principal Full-Stack Software Engineer, WebGL/Three.js Specialist, and Web3 Integrator specializing in Neurotech.

Project Overview: Build "NeuroSim Web3", a full-stack educational platform for interactive 3D brain anatomy exploration and neurosurgery simulation.

Architecture & Tech Stack:

Frontend: Vite, React (TypeScript), Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui.

Animations: animejs (and @types/animejs). Use this exclusively for all UI transitions and 3D property animations (e.g., lerping camera positions, fading mesh opacities).

3D Engine: @react-three/fiber and @react-three/drei.

Backend: Node.js, Express, CORS, dotenv.

Database: MongoDB Atlas.

Authentication: Auth0 (@auth0/auth0-react & Express middleware).

Web3: Solana (@solana/web3.js, @solana/wallet-adapter-react).

Strict Security Directives:

NEVER expose API keys in the frontend code.

All calls to Snowflake, Gemini (Gemma 4), and ElevenLabs MUST be securely routed through the Node.js backend.

Expect all API keys to be provided in a root .env file. Do not mock API keys; use process.env.

Integration Requirements (Hackathon Sponsors):

Auth0 AI Agents: Secure the main application and manage agent-to-user interactions. Only authenticated users can access the simulator, and the backend must verify the Auth0 token before allowing the AI Mentor to access the user's specific progress data.

MongoDB Atlas: Create a NeuroProgress Mongoose schema to store user profiles, quiz scores, and surgical milestones (e.g., "Craniotomy: 100%").

Snowflake API (RAG Data): Create an Express route /api/neuro-data that uses a single CURL/REST call to Snowflake's API to retrieve complex neurological textbook context (RAG) when a user clicks a specific brain structure.

Gemma 4 (via Gemini API): Create a conversational endpoint /api/mentor utilizing Google's Gemma 4 open-weight model. This acts as the "Chief Neurosurgeon AI Agent," analyzing the user's surgical choices and feeding off the context provided by Snowflake.

ElevenLabs: Create an endpoint /api/audio-guide that takes the Gemma 4 text response and streams a dynamic, human-sounding audio voice to guide the user through high-stress surgical steps.

Solana: Build a Web3 utility to leverage Solana's blazing-fast, zero-cost transactions. When a user completes a surgery, mint a "Certified Virtual Neurosurgeon" on-chain certificate/NFT on the Devnet.

